Q1. Program to Calculate Simple Interest
(a) Problem Analysis
Problem: Calculate Simple Interest.
Inputs:Principal (P),Time (T),Rate (R)
Process:
Use formula:
Simple Interest (SI) = (P × T × R) / 100
Output:
Simple Interest (SI)

(b) Algorithm

step1:Start
step2:Declare variables P, T, R, SI
step3:Input values of P, T, and R
step4:Calculate SI = (P * T * R) / 100
step5:Display SI
step6:Stop